news.title: EV charging points to be must for all buildings except single houses in Uttarakhand
news.para: To promote electric vehicles in Uttarakhand and ensure sufficient charging points for them, the state cabinet on Thursday approved a proposal to amend the Building Construction and Development By-Laws/Regulations, 2011.

news.title: Rs 100 crore 'siphoned' from HSVP secret account to Punjab builders
news.para: The secret bank account is linked to Panchkula’s estate office and the fraudulent transactions are worth more than Rs 100 crore, while the internal audit team has, so far, got to the details of transactions worth Rs 72 crore.

news.title: Punjab announces 2.25% exemption in stamp duty on property registration till Mar 31
news.para: In an official statement, revenue minister Bram Shanker Jimpa said the government has reduced stamp duty and fee by 2.25 per cent from March 1 till March 31.

news.title: CBI closes bank fraud case against Pune Buildtech
news.para: In its final report submitted to a special CBI court after nearly seven months of probe, the central probe agency said it has not found "any malafide intention of borrower to cheat/defraud the bank or to cause wrongful loss to the bank and as such no criminal case is made out against the accused persons".

news.title: Bengaluru: Tenants forced out after Canara Bank cracks down on building owner
news.para: Officials from Canara Bank claimed that the owner, identified as SM Shivanna, had provided surety for a Rs 6 crore loan that the bank had disbursed in 2016 to Shanthakumar, a mining businessman in Tumakuru.

news.title: Maharashtra plans to use buildable salt pan lands for rehabilitation & redevelopment
news.para: Unless we use them for rehabilitation or Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana, we will not be able to speedily develop SRA projects or achieve other rehabilitation projects in Mumbai, said deputy chief minister Devendra Fadnavis

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP revokes order to cancel licence of MRG Skyline
news.para: Officials from the department said the cancellation order was revoked after the developer, KN Infracon Pvt Limited, paid the requisite fee.

news.title: China Vanke raises nearly $500 million in Hong Kong share sale
news.para: State-backed Vanke said in a filing that it sold 300 million shares at HK$13.05 per share, versus their offer price range of between HK$12.93 to HK$13.20 apiece, according to the term sheets of the deal launched on Wednesday and seen by Reuters.

news.title: House prices in UK fall by 1.1% in February 2023
news.para: The 1.1% fall was the biggest year-on-year drop since November 2012 and also the first annual decrease since June 2020, early in the coronavirus pandemic, when prices edged down by 0.1%, Nationwide said.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing's Rs 900-crore NCD issue opens on Friday
news.para: The base size of the issue is only Rs 100 crore with a greenshoe option for an additional Rs 800 crore. The public issue opens on Friday and closes March 17, Indiabulls Housing Finance said in a statement.

news.title: Blackstone blocked investor withdrawals from $71 billion REIT in February
news.para: ​BREIT said it fulfilled redemption requests of $1.4 billion in February, which represents only 35% of the approximately $3.9 billion in total withdrawal requests for the month, the firm said in a letter to investors.

news.title: Dhauli Heights houses to be handed over soon: Odisha co-operation minister
news.para: The residential project taken up by Odisha Cooperative Housing Corporation (OCHC) was launched in 2014, but the allottees are yet to get their flats.

news.title: Punjab to start 18 more public sand mines
news.para: As per records, during the last three weeks after the inauguration of the sand supply at Rs 5.50 per cubic feet, the public has used 1.99 lakh metric tonnes (LMT) of sand through 19,516 trolleys.

news.title: MahaRERA probe finds 1,781 bank accounts linked to multiple projects, issues notices
news.para: The Real Estate (Regulation & Development) Act, 2016, makes it mandatory to have a single bank account for the project under one registration number. This is aimed at proper completion of the registered housing projects without any diversion of funds.  1,781 projects have violated the rules by linking their bank accounts to more than one project.

news.title: Madras HC pat for Tamil Nadu fiat on registration of property
news.para: Though the action has been taken after several court orders addressing the issue, Madras high court has appreciated the timely action taken on part of the registration department in issuing the circular without complicating the issue by moving appeals against the order.
